1
00:01:22,248 --> 00:01:26,116
For we meet in an hour
of change and challenge,

2
00:01:26,219 --> 00:01:29,086
in a decade of hope and fear,

3
00:01:29,189 --> 00:01:32,386
in an age of both
knowledge and ignorance.

4
00:01:32,492 --> 00:01:37,520
The greater our knowledge increases,
the greater our ignorance unfolds.

5
00:01:37,630 --> 00:01:40,622
So it is not surprising

6
00:01:40,733 --> 00:01:44,567
that some would have us
stay where we are a little longer.

7
00:01:44,671 --> 00:01:47,162
To rest, to wait.

8
00:01:47,273 --> 00:01:51,141
But this city of Houston,
this state of Texas,

9
00:01:51,244 --> 00:01:53,235
this country of the United States

10
00:01:53,346 --> 00:01:57,749
was not built by those who waited and
rested and wished to look behind them.

11
00:02:02,689 --> 00:02:05,089
We choose to go to the Moon.

12
00:02:05,191 --> 00:02:07,159
We choose
to go to the Moon--

13
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:17,536
We choose to go to the Moon
in this decade and do the other things,

14
00:02:17,637 --> 00:02:21,767
not because they are easy,
but because they are hard.

15
00:02:21,875 --> 00:02:23,843
[Matt Johnson]
With this one speech,

16
00:02:23,943 --> 00:02:29,245
John F. Kennedy escalated our Cold War
with the Soviet Union to outer space.

17
00:02:29,349 --> 00:02:32,716
Now, if we do not land a man
on the Moon by 1969,

18
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:35,287
we will have broken JFK's promise.

19
00:02:35,388 --> 00:02:39,256
And in the eyes of the world,
the Soviet Union will win the Cold War.

20
00:02:39,359 --> 00:02:41,190
To make matters even more difficult,

21
00:02:41,294 --> 00:02:44,786
the CIA has discovered a leak
coming out of the space program.

22
00:02:44,898 --> 00:02:48,231
Top secret American research
is showing up in Soviet briefings,

23
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:53,533
which means the KGB has implanted
a mole inside NASA.

24
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:55,767
If the Russians are able
to steal our technology,

25
00:02:55,875 --> 00:02:58,366
they could beat us to the Moon,

26
00:02:58,478 --> 00:03:02,972
just as they beat us into space
with the Sputnik satellite in 1957.

27
00:03:04,317 --> 00:03:07,445
The director of NASA, James Webb,
denies the presence of this mole,

28
00:03:07,554 --> 00:03:11,650
which means the CIA must move
in a team undercover.

29
00:03:11,758 --> 00:03:13,851
That's where we come in.

30
00:03:14,894 --> 00:03:17,624
Allow me to introduce
Owen Williams,

31
00:03:17,730 --> 00:03:20,597
and myself, Matt Johnson.

32
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:22,827
We joined the CIA through
the Bright Recruits program

33
00:03:22,936 --> 00:03:25,837
and have been working together
ever since.

34
00:03:25,939 --> 00:03:31,309
Along with our camera team,
we make up the CIA's AV Department.

35
00:03:31,411 --> 00:03:34,403
Currently, we are finishing
Operation Deep Red:

36
00:03:34,514 --> 00:03:36,709
The probe into film director
Stanley Kubrick.

37
00:03:36,816 --> 00:03:40,684
But this mission is not using us
to our full potential.

38
00:03:40,787 --> 00:03:44,120
We are asking to be transferred off
of Operation Deep Red,

39
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:46,419
and on to Operation Zipper:

40
00:03:46,526 --> 00:03:48,790
The mission into NASA
to find the mole.

41
